25. AI LIMIT PROTECTION SYSTEM
IMPORTANT
All AI tools must work modularly.
Never allow full project rewrites.

UNIVERSAL AI DEVELOPMENT RULES
IMPORTANT DEVELOPMENT RULES:
Work modularly.
Never rewrite unrelated sections.
Never regenerate the whole project unless requested.
Maintain consistency with the existing design system.
Preserve responsiveness.
Preserve dark/light mode compatibility.
Keep animations performant and cinematic.
Use reusable architecture.
Keep components isolated.
Use clean file organization.

26. SAFE STOP SYSTEM
IMPORTANT
When approaching context/token limit:
AI must stop safely before corruption.

SAFE STOP COMMAND
If approaching token/context limit:
STOP IMMEDIATELY and output:
COMPLETED WORK
MODIFIED FILES
CURRENT FILE STATUS
REMAINING TASKS
LAST SAFE CHECKPOINT
NEXT STEP TO CONTINUE
Then wait for:
CONTINUE FROM CHECKPOINT

27. RESUME COMMAND
CONTINUE COMMAND
CONTINUE FROM CHECKPOINT
Use:
previous architecture,
previous animations,
previous components,
previous design system,
and continue ONLY unfinished work.
Do NOT rewrite completed sections.

28. CRITICAL MODULAR RULE
Every section must:
have isolated logic,
isolated animation,
isolated styling,
and isolated component structure.
This prevents:
corruption,
duplication,
and animation conflicts.

